text: Sleeping (hahaha), playing mobile games, walking, running, and trying new cafes.. During my senior high school years, I was more inclined toward politics. As a HUMSS graduate, politics naturally caught my attention—especially during the pandemic, when it became a loud and relevant topic. I found myself being vocal about what I stood for.. I am most passionate about learning, so I studied hard and joined almost all the extra-curricular activities in school, even though they were held online. Maybe it was because I was just really bored?. As I’ve said, I was really into politics during my senior high school years. What really caught my curiosity was understanding how the system works—like how senators works, how the branches of government operate, and honestly, how messed up and flawed it can be. It was eye-opening, and it made me more vocal about my beliefs and more interested in how change can actually happen.. I didn’t really have any specific career goals in mind when I enrolled in my program because, to be honest, it was never really my first choice. I just went with the flow and tried to make the most out of the opportunity I had.
